SUMMARY: TORONTO TRANSIT COMMISSION (TTC) BOARD
DESCRIPTION:Attend the Meeting: TTC Board meetings are conducted in a hyb
 rid format\, allowing for both in-person attendance at Toronto City Hall 
 and virtual participation. Meetings are live-streamed and archived on the
  TTC's YouTube Channel.\n\nMake a Deputation (Speak at the Meeting): To a
 ddress the Board\, register in advance by emailing commissionservices@ttc
 .ca mailto:commissionservices@ttc.ca . Include your name\, any organizati
 on you represent\, the agenda item number and title\, and a brief descrip
 tion of your remarks. Registration deadline: 12:00 p.m. (noon) the busine
 ss day before the meeting.\n\nSubmit Written Correspondence: Email commis
 sionservices@ttc.ca mailto:commissionservices@ttc.ca . Include your name\
 , any organization you represent\, and clearly reference the agenda item 
 number and title.\n\nView Agendas & Meeting Materials: secure.toronto.ca/
 council/#/highlights http://secure.toronto.ca/council/#/highlights (searc
 h TTC Board)\n\nFull Participation Guide: ttc.ca/about-the-ttc/the-board/
 engaging-with-the-ttc-board-and-committees http://ttc.ca/about-the-ttc/th
 e-board/engaging-with-the-ttc-board-and-committees\n\nAccessibility Accom
 modations: accessibility@toronto.ca mailto:accessibility@toronto.ca | (41
 6) 392-5431\n\nStay informed on Ward 23 news\, subscribe to Councillor My
 ers' newsletter at jamaalmyers.com http://jamaalmyers.com
