SUMMARY: Piano Party
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the stunning restoration of Cathedral Bluffs’ herit
 age grand piano with a joyful and inspiring evening that brings together 
 exceptional young soloists and timeless orchestral masterworks. This spec
 ial concert highlights rising talents from local music festivals and valu
 ed community partners\, performed alongside the orchestra in a celebratio
 n of musical excellence\, collaboration\, and the future of classical mus
 ic.\n\nThe program opens with Vivaldi’s Violin Concerto No. 1 in E major\
 , “La primavera (Spring)” from The Four Seasons\, performed by violinist 
 Tina Sievers\, Concerto Winner of the 2025 North York Music Festival. Sai
 nt-Saëns’ elegant and dramatic Piano Concerto No. 2 in G minor\, Andante 
 sostenuto\, follows\, featuring pianist Michael Jia\, Concerto Winner of 
 the 2025 CCC Toronto International Music Festival. The evening continues 
 with Beethoven’s powerful Piano Concerto No. 3 in C minor\, Allegro con b
 rio\, performed by pianist Karen Yoshida\, Concerto Winner of the 2025 No
 rth York Music Festival. The concert concludes with Florence Price’s Symp
 hony No. 1 in E minor\, a landmark work that blends rich Romantic traditi
 on with a distinctive and compelling American voice.
